Diagram of impact assessment due to changes in climatology and perturbation. The triangles and circles indicate the boundary conditions and corresponding RCM outputs for each experiment, respectively. Δ is the future precipitation change estimated using the direct dynamical downscaling (DDS) method. ΔP and ΔC represent the contributions of changes in the perturbation and climatology, respectively. The expected climate change is defined by the sum of ΔP
0 and ΔC
0. Δcp is the difference between the actual and expected future climates

